observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor ensure that all procurement activities undertaken by the LGU are strictly in accordance with the provisions of the 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184, to ensure the regularity of the procurement process and the award of the contracts.
We also recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the:
Bids and Awards Committee and the Technical Working Group to:                    (i) immediately submit all the lacking Bidding Documents to the Municipal Accountant, for the eventual submission to the Audit Team; (ii) be cautious in the evaluation and assessment of the eligibility as to legal, technical and financial capacities of the prospective bidders; and (iii) adopt in the succeeding procurements, the prescribed template for the Bidding Forms under the 6th edition Philippine Bidding Documents;
Municipal Engineer to: (i) ensure that detailed engineering activities on all infrastructure projects are sufficiently carried-out, pursuant to Annex A of 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184; (ii) closely monitor the projects to ensure that these are implemented in accordance with the approved plans and specifications and completed within the contract duration; and (iii) ascertain that relevant information on all infrastructure projects are duly posted on the project billboards, pursuant to COA Circular No. 2013-004;
Municipal Accountant to: (i) immediately submit to the Audit Team the lacking supporting documents and ensure that all claims are duly supported with proper and complete supporting documents, as required under COA Circular No. 2012-001, before processing for payment, to establish the validity, regularity and propriety of the transactions; and (ii) prepare the necessary JEV to account for the noted errors in recording, for fair and correct presentation of the affected accounts in the Financial Statements;
Municipal Budget Officer to obligate the full contract cost of the projects once awarded to the winning bidders, pursuant to Section 350 of RA No. 7160, for proper reporting of obligations within the same year it was incurred, and to ensure availability of appropriations for the intended projects; and
Municipal Treasurer to ascertain that payments are received by duly authorized representatives only.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the Municipal Accountant to: 

refrain from granting of additional fund transfers to barangays until all previous fund transfers have been settled/liquidated and accounted for in the books of accounts to prevent accumulation of unliquidated fund transfers;

check the regularity and completeness of supporting documents as required under COA Circular No. 2012-001 before funds are transferred to the barangays;

record fund transfers in the books of accounts as receivable from the concerned barangays subject to liquidation to ensure that funds are used only for the intended purpose; and

submit the DVs together with supporting documents relative to the financial assistance granted to seven (7) barangays for the 68th Founding Anniversary of the Municipality.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor, being the Chairperson of the Municipal DRRM Council cause for the optimal utilization of the LDRRM Fund to strengthen the resilience of the constituents to disaster and climate change impacts. Disbursement against the fund should be in pursuance of RA No. 10121.

We also recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the:

Municipal DRRM Officer to prepare an LDRRMF Investment Plan that includes the unexpended balances from previous years to prioritize their utilization in the ensuing year; 

Municipal Accountant to (i) record the unexpended balance of the LDRRMF to a Special Trust Fund under the Trust Liability-DRRM account in the Trust Fund books pursuant to Section 21 of RA No. 10121, to ensure that funds are available for disaster risk reduction and management activities; and (ii) check the completeness of supporting documents prescribed under COA Circular No. 2012-001 before processing payments to determine compliance with the 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184 and to establish the legality, validity and propriety of the disbursements;

BAC to strictly comply with the provisions of the 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184 to establish the regularity of the procurement process and award of contract/PO; and

MHO to adhere to the provision under PNDF, 8th Edition in the requisition of drugs and medicines.

