We recommended that the Management:

implement priority projects funded out of grants from various entities totaling P8,317,649.76 in accordance with the specific purposes as stated in the Memorandum of Agreements; 
exert diligent effort in locating the documents relating to the long outstanding accounts totaling P1,569,874.26 and/or confirm with the source agencies to know their purpose/s and enable utilization thereof; 
evaluate the need for these unexpended fund balances from NGAs.  Should the funds be proven no longer needed, it should be remitted to the source agencies as required under existing rules and regulations.  If still needed, Management should request authority from the source agency to use the money for other related projects of the Municipality;
maximize utilization of funds coming from the PCSO and STL intended for medical assistance of the poor and marginalized constituents; and 
make representation with source NGAs to download the full amount of financial assistance to replenish the amount spent by the Municipality for the completion of various projects or adjust the negative balances in the books of accounts.

We recommended that:

The Management ensure that programs/projects/activities to be charged against the 20% Development Fund are specifically identified in the AIP to facilitate proper implementation and monitoring. Identify, first and foremost, the programs and projects that must be prioritized for inclusion and consideration in the AIP. For those which are inconsistent with the governing rules and regulations, initiate the amendments to address the needs of the constituents;

The Management faithfully carry out the developmental objectives by which the 20% Development Fund has been created and ensure optimal utilization of the fund for the implementation of projects for the benefit of its constituents.  Projects under this fund should be geared towards the pursuance of development objectives that would lead to the attainment of a truly developed community;

Financial assistance to barangays be recorded in the books of accounts as receivable from the concerned barangays for proper liquidation to ensure that funds are used only for the intended purpose; and

Stop the practice of transferring cash from the 20% Development Fund to other funds without clear intention of returning the amount to prevent depleting the funds for development purposes.

